  "text": "Usually, the antimicrobial compounds have a severe effect on the exposed microorganisms' cells. Generally, the morphological abnormalities of the bacterial cells were observed by scanning electron microscopy [CITATION_1] . On the other hand, formation of extracellular capsular polysaccharides, changes in cell size, and cell division alterations were also determined by analysis of transmission electron microscopy [CITATION_2] .",
